<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="308" type="etymology">
<paragraph blockId="3.[151,1437,150,1077]" pageId="3" pageNumber="308">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,334,1015,1041]" pageId="3" pageNumber="308">Etymology.</emphasis>
The species name is derived from the Latin, 
<emphasis box="[865,985,1015,1041]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="308">barathrum</emphasis>
(= gulf, pit), referring to the hollowed emargination on the ventral margin of valva in the male genitalia.
</paragraph>
